# OPSEC deny-list template (spec Section 11.5).
# Copy to .opsec-terms (git-ignored) and add real entries there.
#
# Format: one term per line. Matching is case-insensitive, fixed-string,
# over UTF-8 text only. Terms of 4 characters or fewer (short
# abbreviations) match on word boundaries only, so they do not
# false-positive inside base64 hashes; they will miss the abbreviation
# embedded inside a longer identifier. Binary and non-UTF-8 files (UTF-16
# exports from office tools) are not scanned; keep those out of the repo.
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Add every term that must never appear in this repo:
#   employer names, current and former
#   client and customer names
#   engagement and project codenames
#   internal initiative and workstream names
#   real program, facility, or product names that must stay out
#
# Never add real entries to this example file. It is committed, so a
# real term added here would itself be the leak.
